AVGN VS Dr. Wily

This game is one of the hardest ROM hacks I've ever made. It's very hard and challenging. This is a Hack sequel to Mega Man II, set after Mega Man defeated Dr. Wily again. Dr. Wily set up a trap to kill Mega Man. Mega Man was subsequently killed by Dr. Wily. So now Dr. Wily rebuilt all eight Robot Masters again, and made all stages much more difficult. However, only one hero can stop the evil Dr. Wily and save the world. He is... Angry Video Game Nerd!

Super Mario Bros. - No Skipping Edition

The Level Design are still the same except there's no 1-Up Mushrooms, no Invincibility Stars, no Vines (that takes you up to Bonus Round), and no 10 Coins. Yes, the coins are still in the game. The Warp Zones are removed too. If you try enter the Warp Zone, you will see the message that says "NO WARP ZONE ALLOWED!". But, if you did enter a Warp Zone, you have to jump down to bottomless pit and die. The underground secret pipes (where you collect more coins) are now change into beginner’s trap. If you enter underground secret pipe, you will end up fall down into bottomless pit and die. Have fun!

Sonic 1 - YOLO Edition

Sonic 1 - YOLO (You Only Live Once) Edition is a harder version of Sonic The Hedgehog 1 for Sega Genesis. - You start off with one life only. - All the rings are removed. - All monitors are now Eggman Monitors, which will kill you when broken. - Checkpoints are removed. - The score system is staying at 0, which means no extra continues. - There are no extra lives or shields. - The debug mode is turned off. - If you try to skip to the next Zone by using the level select code, it will start you off in Green Hill Zone Act 1. - If you die once, then it's Game Over. - The only way to cheat is to use Game Genie codes or using save sates on an emulator. Good luck trying to beat the whole game without dying once.

AVGN VS Ganon

Angry Video Game Nerd VS Ganon is a ROM Hack of The Legend of Zelda: A Link to the Past based on The Angry Video Game Nerd on YouTube. This ROM Hack was a sequel to another ROM Hack "AVGN VS Dr. Wily". After the Angry Video Game Nerd killed Dr. Wily and avenge Mega Man's death. The Nerd found a Time Machine in Dr. Wily's Lab. The Nerd drink too many Rolling Rock Beers while time traveling. The Nerd was too drunk to travel back in time to prevent Dr. Wily killing Mega Man. The Nerd ended up going back in time way too far and ended up killing Link in the land of Hyrule and past out drunk laying in Link's bed. This ROM Hack supports MSU1 with Audio Tracks from The Angry Video Game Nerd Episodes and other games that AVGN reviewed. Plus with FMV of The Angry Video Game Nerd Techno Theme Intro Remix. - The player's lives was set to 1 hit KO. If you get hit once. You're dead! Game Over. - The enemies are now triple less damage. - Most of crack wall marks was removed to make secret areas hard to find. - Most of the dialogues was changed.
